data.title: Prenatal hypertension as the risk of eclampsia, HELLP syndrome, and critical obstetric hemorrhage
data.meta_description: Critical bleeding is a common cause of maternal mortality in obstetric patients. However, the non-obstetric factors underlying critical obstetric bleeding remain uncertain.
